cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with speech synthesis and prosody transfer, which falls under the domain of sound processing. 
2. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper uses a neural text-to-speech synthesizer and proposes a method to incorporate acoustic features into it, which involves language processing. 
3. cs.SD (Signal Processing): The paper deals with processing of speech signals and extracting acoustic features from them. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a neural network-based synthesizer and proposes a method to condition it using acoustic features, which involves machine learning. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel method to achieve prosody transfer using a neural network-based synthesizer, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
